        section#descricao.mt-5
            .container
                .decptext.text-center
                    h1  Food Restoration and Innovation

                .decptext.text-start
                    p.lead.fw-bold The diploma of higher professional technician in Food Restoration and Innovation is awarded to students who demonstrate, in this area:
                    p.lead a) possess knowledge and comprehension skills; 
                    p.lead b) know how to apply, in professional contexts, the knowledge and comprehension skills acquired;
                    p.lead c) have the ability to identify and use information to respond to well-defined concrete and abstract problems;
                    p.lead d) possess skills that enable them to communicate about their understanding of issues, skills and activities with their peers, supervisors and clients;
                    p.lead e) Possess learning skills that allow them to pursue studies with some autonomy.

        section#perfil.mt-5
            .container
                .decptext.text-center 
                    h2 Profile of the study program

                .decptext.text-start
                    p.lead The Higher Professional Technical Course in Catering and Food Innovation aims to provide higher professional qualification that allows planning, directing, coordinating, supervising and controlling the activities and operations of production and service in catering units, performing tasks of a technical kitchen nature and providing the technician with skills in terms of food innovation.

        section#diplomados.mt-5
            .container
                .decptext.text-center 
                    h2 Occupational profile of graduates

                .decptext.text-start
                    p.lead.fw-bold The Higher Technical Professional Course in Catering and Food Innovation is part of the training area of Hotel and Restaurant Management, and its graduates are prepared to perform technical functions, within the scope of the study program profile:
                    p.lead - Plan, manage and coordinate all preparation, confection and distribution operations at the restaurant and catering level;
                    p.lead - Perform technical kitchen tasks, promoting creativity;
                    p.lead - Organize and supervise the conditions and activities related to hygiene and food safety and implement quality control systems with a view to continuous improvement;
                    p.lead - Design and execute promotion and sales activities for different market segments;
                    p.lead - Plan and structure menus and calculate associated costs;
                    p.lead - Manage the information obtained through computer tools in the preparation of reports, kitchen technical sheets and stock management;
                    p.lead - Manage and promote commercial management and negotiation techniques.
                    p.lead - Promote and manage innovation and entrepreneurship in organizations.
                    p.lead - Design new products exploring the physical, chemical and sensory properties of food;
                    p.lead - Coordinate the application of technologies in terms of storage, production and preservation of food products.


